3.1 Descriptive Statistic¶

Looking at the data, we see that the average BMI is about 28.33, but it can be as low as 12.02 or as high as 94.85. People's BMIs vary quite a bit. On average, the score for PhysicalHealth is about 3.37 out of 30, but this varies a lot too. MentalHealth scores, like PhysicalHealth, have a lot of variation with an average score close to 3.90 out of 30. Lastly, people usually sleep about 7.1 hours, but this can be as short as 1 hour or as long as a full day."

In [ ]:
from scipy.stats import chi2_contingency, ttest_ind

def calculate_p_values(df, target_col):
    p_values = {}
    
    for col in df.columns:
        if col != target_col:
            
            if df[col].dtype == 'object':
                contingency = pd.crosstab(df[col], df[target_col])
                _, p, _, _ = chi2_contingency(contingency)
                p_values[col] = p
            
            else:
                group1 = df[df[target_col] == 'Yes'][col]
                group2 = df[df[target_col] == 'No'][col]
                _, p = ttest_ind(group1, group2, nan_policy='omit')
                p_values[col] = p
    
    return p_values

p_values = calculate_p_values(df, 'HeartDisease')
p_values_df = pd.DataFrame(list(p_values.items()), columns=['Feature', 'P-value']).sort_values(by='P-value')
p_values_df

6.1.1 Logistic Regression on Resampled Data(Smote)¶

In [ ]:
lr_nearmiss = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000)
scores_nearmiss = cross_val_score(lr_nearmiss, xtrain, ytrain, cv=5)
avg_score_nearmiss = scores_nearmiss.mean()
print(f"5-Fold Cross-Validated Accuracy (NearMiss with LR): {avg_score_nearmiss:.4f}")

lr_nearmiss.fit(xtrain, ytrain)
y_pred_nearmiss = lr_nearmiss.predict(xtest)

print("Accuracy (NearMiss with LR):", accuracy_score(ytest, y_pred_nearmiss))
print("Precision (NearMiss with LR):", precision_score(ytest, y_pred_nearmiss))
print("Recall (NearMiss with LR):", recall_score(ytest, y_pred_nearmiss))
print("F1 Score (NearMiss with LR):", f1_score(ytest, y_pred_nearmiss))
print("Confusion Matrix (NearMiss with LR):\n", confusion_matrix(ytest, y_pred_nearmiss))

y_prob_nearmiss = lr_nearmiss.predict_proba(xtest)[:,1]
fpr_nearmiss, tpr_nearmiss, thresholds_nearmiss = roc_curve(ytest, y_prob_nearmiss)
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 7))
plt.plot(fpr_nearmiss, tpr_nearmiss, label=f'ROC AUC (NearMiss with LR) = {roc_auc_score(ytest, y_prob_nearmiss):.2f}')
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'r--')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.title('Receiver Operating Characteristic (ROC) Curve with NearMiss using Logistic Regression')
plt.legend(loc='lower right')
plt.show()

print("ROC AUC Score (NearMiss with LR):", roc_auc_score(ytest, y_prob_nearmiss))

In [ ]:
gb_nearmiss = GradientBoostingClassifier()
scores_nearmiss = cross_val_score(gb_nearmiss, xtrain, ytrain, cv=5)
avg_score_nearmiss = scores_nearmiss.mean()
print(f"5-Fold Cross-Validated Accuracy (NearMiss with GB): {avg_score_nearmiss:.4f}")

gb_nearmiss.fit(xtrain, ytrain)
y_pred_nearmiss = gb_nearmiss.predict(xtest)

print("Accuracy (NearMiss with GB):", accuracy_score(ytest, y_pred_nearmiss))
print("Precision (NearMiss with GB):", precision_score(ytest, y_pred_nearmiss))
print("Recall (NearMiss with GB):", recall_score(ytest, y_pred_nearmiss))
print("F1 Score (NearMiss with GB):", f1_score(ytest, y_pred_nearmiss))
print("Confusion Matrix (NearMiss with GB):\n", confusion_matrix(ytest, y_pred_nearmiss))

y_prob_nearmiss = gb_nearmiss.predict_proba(xtest)[:,1]
fpr_nearmiss, tpr_nearmiss, thresholds_nearmiss = roc_curve(ytest, y_prob_nearmiss)
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 7))
plt.plot(fpr_nearmiss, tpr_nearmiss, label=f'ROC AUC (NearMiss with GB) = {roc_auc_score(ytest, y_prob_nearmiss):.2f}')
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'r--')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.title('Receiver Operating Characteristic (ROC) Curve with NearMiss using Gradient Boosting')
plt.legend(loc='lower right')
plt.show()

print("ROC AUC Score (NearMiss with GB):", roc_auc_score(ytest, y_prob_nearmiss))

plt.plot(fpr_smote, tpr_smote, label=f'ROC AUC (SMOTE with GNB) = {roc_auc_score(y_test_smote, y_prob_smote):.2f}')
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'r--')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.title('Receiver Operating Characteristic (ROC) Curve with SMOTE using Gaussian Naive Bayes')
plt.legend(loc='lower right')
plt.show()
